<html><head><meta charset="utf-8"><meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge"><meta content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1, maximum-scale=1, user-scalable=no" name="viewport"><link type="text/css" rel="stylesheet" href="_TheLordTitlesAndRL.css" /></head><body>

<div class="c230_108"> 
<div id="v230.108.1"><span class="H7892 s">A Song</span><span class="H4210 s"> <i>or</i> Psalm</span><span class="H1732 s"> of David</span><span class="H430 s">. O God</span><span class="H3820 s">, my heart</span><span class="H3559 s"> is fixed</span><span class="H7891 s">; I will sing</span><span class="H2167 s"> and give praise</span><span class="H3519 s">, even with my glory</span>.</div> 
<div id="v230.108.2"><span class="H5782 s">Awake</span><span class="H5035 s">, psaltery</span><span class="H3658 s"> and harp</span><span class="H5782 s">: I <i>myself</i> will awake</span><span class="H7837 s"> early</span>.</div> 
<div id="v230.108.3"><span class="H3034 s">I will praise</span><span class="H3068 s"> thee, O LORD</span><span class="H5971 s">, among the people</span><span class="H2167 s">: and I will sing praises</span><span class="H3816 s"> unto thee among the nations</span>.</div> 
<div id="v230.108.4"><span class="H2617 s">For thy mercy</span><span class="H1419 s"> <i>is</i> great</span><span class="H8064 s"> above the heavens</span><span class="H571 s">: and thy truth</span><span class="H7834 s"> <i>reacheth</i> unto the clouds</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (clouds: or, skies)</span></div> 
<div id="v230.108.5"><span class="H7311 s">Be thou exalted</span><span class="H430 s">, O God</span><span class="H8064 s">, above the heavens</span><span class="H3519 s">: and thy glory</span><span class="H776 s"> above all the earth</span>;</div> 
<div id="v230.108.6"><span class="H3039 s">That thy beloved</span><span class="H2502 s"> may be delivered</span><span class="H3467 s">: save</span><span class="H3225 s"> <i>with</i> thy right hand</span><span class="H6030 s">, and answer</span> me.</div> 
<div id="v230.108.7"><span class="H430 s">God</span><span class="H1696 s"> hath spoken</span><span class="H6944 s"> in his holiness</span><span class="H5937 s">; I will rejoice</span><span class="H2505 s">, I will divide</span><span class="H7927 s"> Shechem</span><span class="H4058 s">, and mete out</span><span class="H6010 s"> the valley</span><span class="H5523 s"> of Succoth</span>.</div> 
<div id="v230.108.8"><span class="H1568 s">Gilead</span><span class="H4519 s"> <i>is</i> mine; Manasseh</span><span class="H669 s"> <i>is</i> mine; Ephraim</span><span class="H4581 s"> also <i>is</i> the strength</span><span class="H7218 s"> of mine head</span><span class="H3063 s">; Judah</span><span class="H2710 s"> <i>is</i> my lawgiver</span>;</div> 
<div id="v230.108.9"><span class="H4124 s">Moab</span><span class="H7366 s"> <i>is</i> my washpot</span><span class="H5518 s"> â€ </span><span class="H123 s">; over Edom</span><span class="H7993 s"> will I cast out</span><span class="H5275 s"> my shoe</span><span class="H6429 s">; over Philistia</span><span class="H7321 s"> will I triumph</span>.</div> 
<div id="v230.108.10"><span class="H2986 s">Who will bring</span><span class="H4013 s"> me into the strong</span><span class="H5892 s"> city</span><span class="H5148 s">? who will lead</span><span class="H123 s"> me into Edom</span>?</div> 
<div id="v230.108.11"><span class="H430 s"><i>Wilt</i> not <i>thou</i>, O God</span><span class="H2186 s">, <i>who</i> hast cast us off</span><span class="H430 s">? and wilt not thou, O God</span><span class="H3318 s">, go forth</span><span class="H6635 s"> with our hosts</span>?</div> 
<div id="v230.108.12"><span class="H3051 s">Give</span><span class="H5833 s"> us help</span><span class="H6862 s"> from trouble</span><span class="H7723 s">: for vain</span><span class="H8668 s"> <i>is</i> the help</span><span class="H120 s"> of man</span>.</div> 
<div id="v230.108.13"><span class="H430 s">Through God</span><span class="H6213 s"> we shall do</span><span class="H2428 s"> valiantly</span><span class="H947 s">: for he <i>it is that</i> shall tread down</span><span class="H6862 s"> our enemies</span>.</div></div>

